The state-owned Minerals and MetalsTrading Corp will send a team to Japan next week to negotiatean iron ore export contract for 1987/88 beginning April 1,trade sources said.    Japan, the biggest buyer of Indian iron ore with imports ofaround 23 mln tonnes a year, has asked India to reduce pricesfrom the current average of 18 dlrs a tonne, the sources said.    "Japan has said it may be forced to reduce ore imports fromIndia next year if New Delhi fails to reduce the price," onesource said, but declined to give further details. REUTER&#3;